informationWeCollect.body:
We may collect the following categories of information:

Account Information

When you register for an account using email login, we may collect and store:

* your email address;
* an optional display name;
* a securely stored password hash (we do not store plaintext passwords).

OAuth and Third-Party Login Information

If you sign in using a third-party authentication provider such as Google, we may receive:

* your account identifier from that provider;
* your name;
* your email address;
* your profile image URL; and
* other profile information that you authorize the provider to share.

The exact information received depends on your provider settings and permissions.

Content and Activity Data

We store Content and activity you submit through the Service, including:

* books, pages, sections, and revisions;
* comments, reports, and moderation submissions;
* timestamps of edits and submissions;
* revision history;
* technical metadata necessary to operate and maintain the Service.

Because OpenBook functions similarly to a collaborative wiki, much of this Content may be public by design.

Technical and Log Data

Like most websites, we may automatically collect technical information such as:

* IP addresses;
* browser type and version;
* operating system information;
* device identifiers where applicable;
* request paths and timestamps;
* referring pages and usage patterns;
* authentication and security logs.

This information helps us maintain security, diagnose issues, and improve reliability.

howWeUse.body:
We use collected information for legitimate operational purposes, including:

Authentication and Account Security

We use account and session data to:

* authenticate users;
* maintain login sessions;
* prevent unauthorized access;
* protect accounts and platform security.

Service Operation and Improvement

We use submitted Content and usage information to:

* display and maintain public and private pages;
* support collaboration and revision history;
* generate exports and backups;
* provide notifications where enabled;
* improve usability, reliability, and performance.

Communications

If enabled, we may use your email address to send:

* account verification messages;
* password reset links;
* important service notices;
* transactional notifications related to your account or content.

We do not use transactional email channels for unrelated marketing without appropriate consent where required by law.

Security, Abuse Prevention, and Analytics

We may use technical logs and activity records to:

* detect abuse, spam, fraud, or malicious activity;
* investigate violations of our Terms of Service;
* debug errors and service outages;
* measure aggregate traffic and usage trends.

sharing.body:
We may share information in the following circumstances:

Public Content

Much of the Content you contribute is intended to be publicly visible, including revisions and collaborative contributions.

Please do not submit private information you do not want publicly disclosed.

Service Providers

We may share information with trusted infrastructure providers necessary to operate the Service, such as:

* hosting providers;
* database services;
* authentication providers;
* email delivery providers;
* backup and monitoring services.

These providers process information subject to their own contractual and legal obligations.

Legal and Safety Requirements

We may disclose information where reasonably necessary to:

* comply with legal obligations;
* respond to lawful requests from authorities;
* protect the rights, property, or safety of users, operators, or the public;
* prevent fraud, abuse, or security threats;
* enforce our Terms of Service.

retention.body:
We retain account information and submitted Content for as long as necessary to operate the Service, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and maintain security.

This may include:

* account records while your account remains active;
* archived backups;
* audit and moderation logs;
* revision history of collaborative pages.

Even after edits or account changes, historical revisions may remain preserved for transparency, moderation, abuse prevention, and platform integrity.

rights.body:
Depending on your location and applicable law, you may have rights regarding your personal information, including the right to:

* access your personal data;
* correct inaccurate information;
* request deletion of personal data;
* request export of your data;
* object to or restrict certain processing;
* withdraw consent where processing is based on consent.

To exercise these rights, use the published contact method for the operator.

Some requests may be limited where retention is necessary for legitimate interests, legal compliance, fraud prevention, moderation history, or preservation of collaborative records.
